#removing outliers with IQR
def remove_outliers(df):
    # Filter only numeric columns
    numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns
    numeric_data = df[numeric_cols]

    # Calculate the first and third quartiles (Q1 and Q3)
    Q1 = numeric_data.quantile(0.25)
    Q3 = numeric_data.quantile(0.75)

    # Calculate the interquartile range (IQR)
    IQR = Q3 - Q1

    # Define the lower and upper bounds for outliers
    lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR

    # Identify and remove outliers
    outliers = ((numeric_data < lower_bound) | (numeric_data > upper_bound))
    cleaned_df = df[~outliers.any(axis=1)]

    return cleaned_df

#Apply MLR
X = np.column_stack((cleaned_df['Carbohydrates (g)'], cleaned_df['Protein (g)'], cleaned_df['Fiber (g)'],
                     cleaned_df['Sugar (g)'], cleaned_df['Total Fat (g)'], cleaned_df['Saturated Fat (g)'],
                     cleaned_df['Cholesterol (mg)'], cleaned_df['Sodium (mg)']))

# Add a constant term to the predictor matrix
X_with_intercept = sm.add_constant(X)

# Create the formula for OLS
formula = 'Q("Energy (kCal)") ~ Q("Carbohydrates (g)") + Q("Protein (g)") + Q("Fiber (g)") + Q("Sugar (g)") + Q("Total Fat (g)") + Q("Saturated Fat (g)") + Q("Cholesterol (mg)") + Q("Sodium (mg)")'

# Create the OLS model using the formula
model = sm.OLS.from_formula(formula, data=cleaned_df)

# Fit the model
results = model.fit()

# Print the summary
print(results.summary())

def convert_percentage_to_int(val):
    if pd.isna(val):
        return val
    if '%' in str(val):
        return int(float(val.rstrip('%')))
    else:
        return int(val)

# Convert 'Per Serve Size' to numeric
cleaned_df['Per Serve Size'] = pd.to_numeric(cleaned_df['Per Serve Size'], errors='coerce')

# Function to normalize each variable to the range [0, 1]
def normalize(df):
    result = df.copy()
    for feature_name in df.columns:
        max_value = df[feature_name].max()
        min_value = df[feature_name].min()
        result[feature_name] = (df[feature_name] - min_value) / (max_value - min_value)
    return result

# Normalize the nutritional values per serving
df_normalized = normalize(cleaned_df[cleaned_df.columns[4:]])

# Calculate the sum of normalized nutritional values
cleaned_df['Nutrition Score'] = df_normalized.sum(axis=1)

# Calculate average nutrition score for each company
avg_nutrition_score = cleaned_df.groupby('Company')['Nutrition Score'].mean().reset_index()

# Plot the bar plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(avg_nutrition_score['Company'], avg_nutrition_score['Nutrition Score'], color='skyblue')
plt.xlabel('Company')
plt.ylabel('Average Nutrition Score')
plt.title('Average Nutrition Score by Company')
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')  # Rotate x-labels for better readability
plt.tight_layout()  # Adjust layout to prevent clipping of labels
plt.show()
